text: Terrible experience with Dr Nguyen Thi Tuyet Anh. I brought my wife there earlier this month and she’s currently at the month of eight. We have some concerns about C section and natural procedure. Dr Nguyen Thi Tuyet Anh was quite rude by her way of approach, challenged the patient back without giving proper consultation. She was also rushing to wrap up the session since knowing we may not pick Hanh Phuc hospital when birth delivery. The service is poor and not up to the level of pricing. We went to AIH with the same situation and have completely different experiences. Hence, we ended up with AIH eventually.

I am a TAIWANESE My wife and I lived here for birth the baby The cost is not cheap I spent about 80 million But worth it There was a Pediatrician stay with my wife and body checkup for my baby And reported to me the situation of baby The doctor explained the situation of baby patiently and carefully This is my first kid,I am nervous and at a loss The nurse here assistanced me a lot The most important is I trust the hospital I had been to many hospitals in VIET NAM I feel most of them tried to perfunctory me But this hospital reaching Taiwan's medical level Any way,if you have sufficient budget,here is a good choose But the meal there is not delicious,haha
Clean and good services. However, it maybe more expensive than others.

This is NOT an international hospital. None of the staff can speak English beyond a "hello" and some poorly stringed together words. The nurses are very forgetful and make frequent mistakes, at least a couple a day. You will need to make sure you check if they did what is scheduled every day. The meals and rooms are great, and the doctors are very good at surgery however. You will pay for services you don't necessarily use as part of a "deposit". The "deposit" is non-refundable, so be prepared to accept that. It is small money end of the day, but a bit of a disgusting predatory practice.
Should have find another hospital. There are always some rooms for improvement.

My wife and I are very happy with our experience in giving birth with hang phuc hospital and the Drs and Nurse there. They are patient, kind and nice & not forceful when it comes to add-ons and provide helpful suggestions. Thank you once again for taking care of us and pray that God will take care of the staff there as they take care of us. 😊

Avoid if you can. We were prescribed a procedure, and on the day we came, it turns out the procedure is not needed anymore. Guess what: we still have to pay for it. They already charged the money on the card on the day of the prescription, so we have no recourse. A well orchestrated scam. A few words on the morning we spent there: nurses are overall uncooperative, doctors say something, then nurse comes and refuse to execute, then another doctor comes and contradict the first doctor, then rinse and rewind, the whole morning, a mess, and a waste of everybody's time. Special mention to Dr. Riche who prescribed it all: unnecessary hospitalization, procedure that never happened, and had no problem telling us "a package is a package" to justify that we pay it all regardless.
Built on 2007, this service hospital absolutely satisfy client.

The overall service is ok. We were happy with our doctor, Dr. Hồ Nguyên Tiến, who guided us through the procedure from pregnancy to delivery and made us feel safe. Highly recommend Dr Tiến. However, my husband and I were not satisfied with the hospital’s pediatrician service for newborn. No clear nor proper explanation about baby’s vaccines and procedures, about must-do tests and optional tests for a new born. My husband is not Vietnamese and I had to do the translation for nurses many times right after delivery. For pediatricians, I recommend Dr Vinh and Dr Thien An; they are experienced, dedicated, and English speaking pediatricians. Also, if you need something while at the hospital, always ask for it. I had to ask for a baby’s vaccination tracking book in English because initially they only provided the Vietnamese book.

If you don’t provide the specific treatment, you should clarify first through the phone when I was making the appointment! Not until we took our long way there and was ready for the treatment but then was rejected by you. Such a waste of time getting there. The staff didn’t even come to us and explain the situation but just let us wait and wait and wait until we asked. It’s a very disappointing experience.

Very poor communication. English is not spoken here. A lot of miss communications. I expect from a “Singapore standard” hospital at least that some people speak English. A lot of things were not done to my newborn, for example hearing test and eye test. They didn’t even tell us that it wasn’t done. A lot of confusion with hospital and health insurance, who pays and what needs to be done. Unorganized. I reached out to their customer service line, they called me, but they showed no empathy nor understood my concerns, being in a different country with such circumstances. Asked to talk to senior management of hospital and they told me they will arrange someone to talk but never did. I recommend other families to look out for an alternative hospital to give birth in Saigon.

Overall a positive experience. Much better quality facilities and services than what is offered in state run hospitals, but you pay for it. On the downside, the English skills of the staff aren't quite up to expected standards and the place nickle and dimes you for extra services to rack up the fees.

Dr Riche over charges and does not give good service especially when you are in an emergency situation regarding birth control. Took 6 days for a response that wasn't helpful at all he barley read my email as he reccomended the EXACT medication I stated in my email was causing problems. Disgusted is an understatement.
Service is ok and most of staff speak English

The quality of doctors is going down since Hanh Phuc was acquired by Hoan My. Not only my wife but also other patients feel the same. There is a woman had to go to Mekong to recover her minor surgery after giving birth at Hanh Phuc in April,2018.
Good place for any mom to get birth here. Good service and an acceptable price.
Poor service in every way... mistakes on charged prices can be seen often... check your bill carefully... Doctors and nurses are lacking of professional knowledges
Good
Bad services. Cant compare with FV. Nurses dont support patients.
Plenty of grateful for doctors, nurses and services.
My child born here :)
ok
Park your bike at the end of the hall to avoid scratches from other bikes
Good hospital in Binh Duong and HCMC

Feeling like being cheated. I was born here because it's close to home. I also thought about many places to vx vx for my child and heard that vx injections here cost money for examination, so I took my child for the first vaccination here to see what it was like before deciding to buy a vaccination package for my child.  The first time I got vaccinated, I went to the registration counter and the person who greeted me said, "Mom, do you want a regular check-up or a quick check-up, a quick check-up with a doctor to see if your baby qualifies for the vx injection or not and doesn't cost money for the check-up?" I chose to have a quick examination because there was nothing wrong with my child, so I needed a thorough examination. I thought I could choose "free examination and paid examination", in the end I chose to buy the injection package here because it was close to home, I paid 20 million.  The second time I got vaccinated, I realized that the quick check-up at the hospital was no longer implemented and now it costs money to get a mandatory check-up. I feel like I'm being manipulated, I feel inhibited, there's nothing my child can do, I forced him to spend 400k on examination but it doesn't solve any problem, I accidentally paid 20 million, the hospital won't let me get it back, what should I do now? Star. Is the hospital putting me in a position where I have to pay extra money every time I get an injection for my child (a package that I had to pay 20 million in advance for). Grit your teeth ok, comfort yourself, think that every time you get vaccinated, your child will be examined by a doctor.  For the 3rd injection, I called the switchboard to make an appointment. The operator said, this afternoon there was no more standard doctors (examination fee 500k, after the increase in examination fees), only senior doctors were available, you explained for another month. Then many doctors were promoted to senior level (the examination fee for a senior doctor is 650k). Do you feel like you're being put in a world where you have to get money for the hospital? Oh, I don't need to see a high-level doctor. It's the hospital's job for the hospital to give you a promotion or something. Why make the patient pay more for the doctor when the hospital ordains it themselves? Is it possible that the hospital doesn't have standard doctors but only has high-level doctors and then forces patients to pay more? I forced my friend over there to tell me to go to the examination area for my child, not the vaccination area anymore.  For examining and injecting VX for my child at HP, I accept paying higher fees than other hospitals. However, I absolutely hate the way the hospital extorts money and leads customers by the nose like that. Advise mothers to consider vxing their children at VNVC or Long Chau to avoid wasting money on armpit examinations, which costs a few million more but doesn't solve any problem.  Sharing about giving birth here, my water broke at 39 weeks, I went to the hospital to induce labor, I waited for the baby to have enough stools before giving birth. When I went into the operating room at 7pm, the midwife followed me from start to finish ( This girl is nice), switching shifts with another girl looks very chubby, I don't know if she's supporting me or abusing me. When I was about to give birth (9pm) and in the delivery room there were only my husband and I and her, she said, "My duty is over, it's yours". What's wrong everyone?????? Well, I haven't given birth yet, so what do you mean your duties are over? I don't understand, I'm just confused, I think I'm in an international hospital but maybe it's still negative. When it was almost time to give birth, the doctor hadn't come in yet. She put her hand in to measure how many inches had expanded. She told me to push, putting her hand in there made me very, very sore. I was scared and tired, losing all my energy. Because of her weight, she lost strength during childbirth and couldn't push hard. I thought, "Oh great, it's not like the doctor delivered the baby, but why is it only this one woman, it's so important to deliver the baby, why is it only this one woman doing it?"" But she hurt me so much, everyone, it's my first time giving birth. So I don't know how many people are needed to support me, how to support me, and what the process is. Only when the doctor came in did I stop being afraid, because I was too scared to be alone with her. Doctor come in and do it gently for me. The doctor who helped me was Dr. Tuyet Anh. After giving birth, when I got home, I tried again. I guess it was because I didn't provide training for that fat midwife that's why I was in pain. huhu

The second time giving birth at the hospital was quite disappointing. On the profile, it was said that the doctor had 5 years - 10 years of experience, but when she entered the delivery room, the birth canal was painless and the doctor stood there instructing an intern to do it. The needle was so long and painful that I kept pulling it out and injecting it again 3-4 times. Spending a large amount of money to give birth at an international hospital but having a pretty bad experience, the service is getting worse and worse. Any mother who intends to give birth here should reconsider.

I took my wife for a prenatal check-up at Happiness Hospital when she was 11 weeks and 2 days pregnant. The doctor did not advise doing double tests to screen for fetal abnormalities, but instead scheduled a follow-up visit 2 weeks later to measure nuchal translucency. The doctor deliberately missed the golden time to do double tests to be able to detect birth defects early. Instead, the doctor chose to measure nuchal translucency, which is very bad for the fetus and when the fetus is 13 weeks and 2 days old (for pregnant women). For mothers over 40 years old) an additional NIPT test is required (very expensive). My husband and I had a very bad experience at happiness hospital.

Let my wife give birth to 2 babies here *The room is clean, but only for the mother and 1 person to stay (pay extra for extra bed). If you want to stay more, it will be multiplied per person but no extra bed *Eating and drinking have someone ordering and serving them to the room. If you can't eat well, the family will take care of it themselves *Staff and doctors gently inquire and guide *High range prices *The most important part of giving birth left the two babies alone, without a nurse. From time to time, the nurse came in to see how much it had expanded and then came out again. The baby's head was almost out before calling the doctor, like who cares? The baby was probably born and the doctor hadn't arrived yet. The doctor who helped me the next time criticized the doctor who helped me last time for bad luck and then cut the milk again for me (beautiful).

Very satisfied with the delivery service at Hanh Phuc Hospital, the medical team is very dedicated and professional, giving birth is like going to rest. With the cost of giving birth in HP, I find it very worth it.

The first time I gave birth to my 1st child in 2018, it was ok, I was just a little dissatisfied with the nurse. The second time it was a bad experience, everyone. From examination services to birth. My second baby was born in October 2023. When I went to see the doctor, I felt like there were fewer patients than the first time, but I didn't think much of it. The receptionist was making mistakes with paperwork. Giving birth cost 70 million but the experience was extremely bad. Do The gif also appeared The fees and service are so bad. I was born right at the time the surgeon gave me leave, so when I was discharged from the hospital, I was not re-examined or asked anything. mac even though the birth package has this item. haizz Everyone should not be born here. It's not worth the money, that is, I'll have to issue the paperwork and get it done insurance but wrong from the hospital. I went home 5-6 times, quad was tired, the nurse talked to me like I was yelling at her, worried. What else is there to say?

The pediatric clinic is extremely bad, with some patients waiting more than 1 and a half hours to be examined. There is no table of order numbers or records for the nurses to self-ordinate calling names into the room, there is a situation where the last records are pushed to the front. The atmosphere in the waiting area for names to be called is stuffy, like getting into a car with a fan without turning on the AC, but having to sit in that area to wait for your name to be called manually. It feels like the medical examination process at this hospital is going backwards. When I registered for the examination, I asked if there was a vip examination, but I said no. I registered for a normal examination, and after waiting for 1 and a half hours, I said there was a doctor... As a senior doctor, the examination fee is higher. If you see that doctor, you will be examined immediately. I don't know if there are any negatives here.

My name is Do Thi Ngoc Hoa. I came back to visit Vietnam last week and went to Vinmec for a gynecological examination and discovered that I had a very large uterine fibroid, but I heard that Dr. Ho Nguyen Tien, obstetrician at Hanh Phuc Hospital, is very good. I went to Hanh Phuc to ask the doctor to examine me and he enthusiastically guided and arranged for me to have an early surgery. The surgery was successful on January 2 and I was discharged from the hospital on January 4. Thank you very much Dr. Tien. Vietnam needs more good and dedicated doctors like Dr. Tien to give patients peace of mind.

Start your journey with Hanh Phuc Hospital from the first week of prenatal check-up until your baby's birth. Overall costs are relatively stable compared to the average level of international hospitals. During prenatal examination, it is up to the doctor to choose to follow until the birth. If you take the initiative then it is good, if not, the staff will advise, but no matter who you choose, you can rest assured because when the examination finds anything unusual, a specialist will be involved. The examination schedule will have to be according to the doctor's schedule, so sometimes conflicts with personal schedules will be accepted. Registering documents is quite quick, but there is also a problem with data synchronization when staff forget to update medical records into the system, leading to records not matching when admitted to the hospital, and having to communicate in circles. Evaluating the examination service for nearly 9 months as good, ignoring minor incidents due to human problems that are difficult to avoid. The quality of the birth package service is good, just bring clothes and personal items, the hospital takes care of all the prenatal examinations, delivery, postpartum... as long as you pay enough money. The nurses' offices are on duty 24/7, providing enthusiastic support when requested, but the stalls and teen rooms are open during business hours, so if you need to buy anything late at night, you can buy it yourself outside. The hospital has a cool green campus, large parking lot, and enthusiastic staff. If the room is opposite the bridge, you can hear the noise of cars at night. The air conditioner uses the same cooling system for the whole area, so the temperature adjustment is not accurate. Overall, the natural birth package for mother and baby is of good quality and quite satisfied with the 3-day stay here.

I think the hospital should change its name to Waiting International. I'm afraid that going to a public hospital will have to wait. In the end, International is no different. Make an appointment in advance but still have to wait at least 1 and a half to two and a half hours. The shift arrangement is completely haphazard and not logical at all. It's clean and the staff is a little considerate. The doctor examined quickly and gave quick advice as if he wanted to dismiss the patient Price does not match the quality. The consulting doctor was outside the reception desk and someone else listened to everything about my illness. The receptionist took information right at the counter while there were many people waiting. There is not a single bit of security. So boring.
The medical team is very dedicated and enthusiastic. The campus is clean and airy. Modern equipment.

High costs but bad, arrogant attitude. I don't know who is the guest, and who is the waiter. The doctor is quiet, examines quickly and then dismisses the patient. Receptionist has bad attitude. Here, I think Dr. Tuan is the best. I have examined Dr. Tuan many times.

International Standard Hospital specializing in Obstetrics and Pediatrics in Thuan An area, Binh Duong (bordering Ho Chi Minh City). The space is clean and airy with the fresh green color of trees. You will not feel like you are in a hospital but at a resort. In particular, the hospital has also joined Hoan My Medical Group to improve service quality as well as meet the health care needs of the people.

The cost is too high compared to the expertise and service, the whole hospital has a few staff but most of the babies after birth have to stay in the special care room (is this the culture of the hospital or the quality of expertise?? ??), the baby had a torn scalp after birth but the family was not given an explanation or accepted responsibility from the hospital. I think this hospital's highest expertise is exploiting the patient's pockets🫡

Registering to stay for another family member was charged 330k/person. I asked for an extra pillow to prevent the baby from falling out of bed, but that was also an extra charge. It was really too much. The price was just right, so now I have to sleep. no pillows. Oh, "Happiness" hospital
High costs, lots of extra costs, every little extra cost is also an additional fee, room with door has a nice evening view

1. When I examined the doctor, I declared the insurance documents right from the beginning. The staff received the documents and asked if there were 2 fees: 550k and 650K (if examined by a specialist). I chose the 650K package. When calculating, an invoice was issued for 780K. (call this the insurance price), even though you don't have to pay, you see a lack of transparency, like a scam (false claim). 2. Spend 780K/visit to wait 1.5 hours. There is no order number for medical examination, waiting for nurses to arrange in an orderly manner (people arriving later are examined first). I don't understand why technology has fallen so far behind? 3. When hospitalized, calculate all the costs: blood tests, syringes, tools, etc. to get as much money as possible from the patient. 4. I booked a 2-bed room priced at 2,280K/night including 3 meals, admitted to the hospital at 8pm the night before, given 1 bowl of porridge in the evening, 1 bowl of noodles the next morning, discharged the next day and waited until the end of the day. I just finished the procedure in the afternoon. I asked if I would pay for the third meal at noon because I'm afraid the baby is hungry. When people come to the hospital, they see the number of vehicles parked outside and the number of patients coming to see them, and they know that once they come, they will never return.
International standard hospital in quality and service. Highly professional, dedicated and dedicated doctors. The ladies take care of the baby and mother very gently and friendly.

International hospitals are so bad in terms of service. Waited more than 90 minutes for medical examination and still no examination At the reception desk, when receiving money and putting it in the file, it will be examined first. I spent money internationally, thinking I was being examined by a government agency Really disappointed with a hospital with an international reputation. Too disappointed. Parents experience this for the first time and understand it thoroughly.
Everything is fine here, fair price = high service
The Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology has good expertise The Department of Pediatrics is okay Price is quite high poor service I will post a detailed review later
Waiting for 1.5 hours for examination, students were crowded. The pediatric examination experience was so bad
The hospital is large and clean like a hotel. The staff and Doctors are very attentive day or night. The price is quite high, if you have good insurance, you can save 80-90% of the cost.
Get pregnant Go to a Motherhood Skills class. The first steps to prepare for your baby. The whole family is looking forward to LeeO, generation F4.

The hospital is located right at the Binh Duong Welcome Gate, below, next to the bridge. The hospital is large, spacious and very quiet. The medical examination and treatment area is clean and modern. However, the cost of examination and inpatient room rental is quite high, according to international hospital prices. There is a large and free parking lot and underground parking lot.
Good service, but the examination cost is quite high compared to the general level. So those who can afford it should come here, otherwise go to the more suitable provincial hospitals.

This is a fairly new medical examination and treatment place but has quite good service quality, capable of reaching 4* quality. The staff service is very good because it is also a favorite place for medical examination and treatment of artists and the rich. The hospital location is right on the riverbank so the air is cool and airy, especially in the afternoon. Spacious and comfortable parking. Try it out and feel it.

No good, I went to get the HPV shot and was forced to go for a gynecological exam. I was going on Friday, so I was absent so I had to wait all morning. At 12 o'clock, the doctor said I couldn't get the shot because I was too old. It was a waste of time.
Service here is good, service prices are high
Everything is good, but hospitals should limit administrative procedures to shorten waiting times.

📣 STAY AWAY FROM THIS HOSPITAL (STAY AWAY THIS HOSPITAL) ENGLISH BELOW  The worst hospital ever seen, even worse than the popular hospital in Dien Bien Phu, Ho Chi Minh City. 1. Room fee is 1,900 million, bed fee for family member is 300,000. It's ok. But the staff said they ran out of beds so they couldn't bring them in. They say they sleep on the sofa. When complaining, the room service lady pushed the bed in. Face with a lot of attitude. The type that doesn't tip money but demands it 2. After the surgery, the family pushed me to the room and for 2 days the doctor came to visit without even looking at the incision but just standing from afar and talking. Then go out and charge 400k 3. Nurses have the attitude that they are a burden to them. 4. Charge for each piece of cotton wool and gauze. Please repeat each piece. Syringes also count. (When I went to other hospitals to use this, they still gave me 1 or 2 syringes to use) 5. When my family member ran out of anesthetic, she was sweating and the bed sheets were wet. Then they brought me new towels I have complete photo evidence. Everyone watched and avoided, the hospital had an international label but had poor personality and attitude. Charge twice as much as others but not inferior to commune hospitals. I hope to never see Hanh Phuc Hospital again .....,.......... But the staff said that all the beds are not brought in. They called to sleep on the sofa. When complaining, the room service sister pushed the bed in. Face very attitude. The kind that doesn't tip money but demands 2. After the operation, the family members pushed them up to the room for 2 days. The doctor came to visit without looking at the incision, but just stood from afar and talked. Done go out and charge 400k 3. The nurses and nurses have a very attitude of being a burden to them. 4. Charge each cotton swab, gauze. Please repeat each piece. Syringes also count. (This one when I went to other hospitals and asked for 1,2 syringes to use, they still gave me) 5. When my family members run out of anesthetic, they sweat and wet the bed sheets. Ask to change the blanket. After changing, I did not clean it, but left it in the room. Ask for a new towel and say it can be washed and reused. I told God what do you think. Then they brought me new towels I have full picture proof. Everyone watched and avoided, the hospital was international but poor in character and attitude. Collecting twice the price of others, but not inferior to the hospital in the ward and commune. Hope to never see you again Hanh Phuc Hospital

International standard hospital but unprofessional behavior. My wife went into labor and requested a cesarean section because the fetus was large. The doctor said it was okay to give birth normally. Until she used the vacuum cleaner twice, the mother was so exhausted that she had to have a cesarean section. When I gave birth, my baby's head was scratched and bleeding. When I left the hospital, I was charged the full price for a normal birth and a cesarean section. It's very unreasonable that I made a comment but no one responded....
Good service, enthusiastic and friendly doctors and nurses
Thanh Tam breeding service. Providing caregivers at good prices, contact 08888.48800. Served 24/24
Piercing the ears of a child with low birth weight can damage the ear canal

I'm here all the time. Honestly, it's a waste of money. Showing all kinds of things, thinking that international fees are high and there are no evils. But if you leave, you won't have time to regret it, all the negative things in the hospital will be gone.
When patients are hungry and discharged from the hospital, they don't need to take visitors to the lobby. Let the patients bring their own things down to the lobby

The doctor's treatment is good, but the service experience is not good. Lost items twice. The first time I forgot my wallet, the hospital contacted me to get it back, but the money was lost. The second time I changed rooms, I lost my earphone. When I went back to look for it, it was gone, which was frustrating
Enthusiastic consulting staff, good consulting and examination doctors, good service, affordable prices when examining children.

Because the translation does not teach instructions, it only says a few sentences. There are instructions in the package, so I don't see any reduction. Not so, but many employees are still too negligent

Took his wife to have a chest x-ray, but there were only 2 male doctors in the room. In addition, he took off his shirt and the doctor held the breasts and placed them on each area to cup. Seems like the wrong process. The doctor could have told the patient to order it. What if his wife is young? Reputable as an international hospital. But it doesn't mean anything. Unlike Tu Du hospital. The Bsi is outside talking with a microphone. And there are instructions and illustrations.
The hospital is beautiful and quite professional!
Operating in an international style, the hospital is very clean and beautiful. Staff are very enthusiastic.
Bad, really really bad. All BV is aiming for is the customer's pocketbook. Instead of being named Hanh Phuc, the hospital should change to "Cuc Tuc" to be true to the hospital's instincts.

Come here for your wife's prenatal check-up. The facilities are very good, but unfortunately, Dr. Nguyen Huu Thuan gave me very cursory and uncaring advice. The test results came back but they didn't report, so I had to call the switchboard to get a text message via zalo. After that, if he wanted to text and ask questions again, he would block the stranger. I will arrange time to go to the hospital again to reflect on this doctor's working attitude. I was planning on having my wife give birth here, but I guess I have to think again!

Examination is too slow, registration from 8:30 am to 10:00 am has not been examined. The staff receiving sick people, calling names are unprofessional, very noisy, without a speaker, making calls is difficult to hear. If you go to the bathroom or go out in the yard, you lose. Wifi is slow
No winning or losing. Money is lost
The hospital's business is slow, wasting customers' time. Completely colored to prevent foot disease.
My two children are always examined and treated here. In general, the professional service is impeccable.
The international hospital called the hotline for 2 days from August 7 to August 8, 2023, but no one picked up the phone! What a POOR SERVICE

I registered to see Dr. Hanh Le at 2:00 p.m. on November 22, 2021 for my 4-month-old baby's symptoms. 1. Frequent constipation for 5-7 days but advice is normal. 2. During pregnancy, the baby was counseled about symptoms of short femurs and now the baby's body looks unbalanced and asked for a check-up, but the doctor only said that because the parents were short, the baby was small and did not check or look at it. Then prescribe calcium and zinc for your baby. What I was concerned about was my child's femur problem, so I took the time to go to a big hospital to get it checked, but I was disappointed. Then prescribe probiotics, zinc and calcium. I went to the hospital from the time I was pregnant until I gave birth, but this visit was so disappointing.
Clean, airy, good service

Extremely unprofessional attitude. The staff sitting at the counter briefly surveys the customer's appearance before working. The other staff also did not have the slightest bit of service. Answered curtly, neglected, just joking and talking in private until we had to speak up. Doctor gives advice through loudspeaker. Preparing for marriage and having a baby but asked where the "family doctor" was, Dr. Th. answer there. When I returned, I was not given an appointment for vaccinations in preparation for having a baby. Waited 2 weeks to get cancer screening results and still didn't get a call to inform them. Money is inherently not easy to earn to find international service quality, but do you want to be as satisfied as I was when I had such an experience at Hanh Phuc? It's not clear what the hospital's business goal is, but it's only open so that employees have to work so forcedly, so where is internationalization and what's the point?

In April 2022, the hospital also applied medical declaration for people coming for examination and accompanying relatives. What is more annoying is that they apply a separate declaration path, so it takes quite a while to fill out the information. I don't understand what the point of such a declaration is at the present time. The step of body temperature screening, which is at least more effective, is not done. Hospitals in Ho Chi Minh City have abandoned the medical declaration step for a long time.
OK, thank you Dr. Tuan's team

I thought a lot before giving feedback on the hospital. I have given birth to a baby and am about to give birth to another baby at the hospital because I trust the hospital again. I monitored my pregnancy throughout the hospital. And the doctor who monitored me was also very thoughtful and caring, like a good doctor, but suddenly 2 days ago I had a stomach ache and went to the emergency room because outside of medical examination hours, the doctor was monitoring.
